{"cmd":"meta","data":{"title":"Costos: ¿Realtime Translate usa Whisper/TTS?"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"g_summary","type":"group","data":{"label":"TL;DR — Tienes razón","icon":"fa-solid fa-lightbulb"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"tldr","type":"note","group":"g_summary","data":{"text":"✅ Correcto: bilingo-meet usa **gpt-realtime-translate** vía `/v1/realtime/translations/calls` (WebRTC). Es un modelo **speech-to-speech nativo** — NO usa Whisper (STT) ni TTS por separado.","color":"#e8f7f0"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"tldr2","type":"note","group":"g_summary","data":{"text":"💰 Pricing: **$0.034 / minuto de audio** (tarifa plana). NO se factura por tokens de Whisper ni por caracteres de TTS. Una llamada de 10 min ≈ $0.34.","color":"#f0f7ff"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"tldr3","type":"note","group":"g_summary","data":{"text":"⚠️ Si en el documento de costos aparecen líneas para **Whisper** y **TTS** separadas, eso refleja la arquitectura *vieja* (STT + MT + TTS en cadena), no la actual. Hay que actualizar el modelo de costos.","color":"#fff7e6"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"g_evidence","type":"group","data":{"label":"Evidencia en el código","icon":"fa-solid fa-code"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"ev1","type":"code","group":"g_evidence","data":{"language":"javascript","title":"public/js/realtimeInterpreter.js — endpoint usado","code":"const modelName = sess.model || 'gpt-realtime-translate';\nconst sdpPath = sess.sdp_path ||\n  (/translate/i.test(modelName)\n    ? '/v1/realtime/translations/calls'\n    : '/v1/realtime/calls');\n// SDP exchange directo con OpenAI — sin Whisper, sin TTS"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"ev2","type":"note","group":"g_evidence","data":{"text":"El flujo es: **audio del peer → mixer → WebRTC track → gpt-realtime-translate → audio traducido (ontrack) → speakers**. Solo hay UNA llamada a OpenAI por sesión. Nunca se invoca `/v1/audio/transcriptions` (Whisper) ni `/v1/audio/speech` (TTS)."}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"ev3","type":"note","group":"g_evidence","data":{"text":"🔎 Donde sí aparece confusión: el schema MySQL todavía tiene columnas legacy `stt_latency_ms`, `mt_latency_ms`, `tts_latency_ms` en `translation_logs` y `translation_sessions`. Son vestigios de la arquitectura previa — hoy solo tendría sentido un único `total_latency_ms` (o `realtime_latency_ms`).","color":"#fff7e6"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"g_findings","type":"group","data":{"label":"Cómo factura OpenAI (mayo 2026)","icon":"fa-solid fa-magnifying-glass"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"f1","type":"note","group":"g_findings","data":{"text":"<cite index=\"7-1,7-2\">Streaming translation and streaming transcription sessions are billed by audio duration. Prices vary per model, with prices listed on the model pages (for example, gpt-realtime-2, gpt-realtime-translate, gpt-realtime-whisper, and gpt-realtime).</cite>\n\nFuente: developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/realtime-costs"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"f2","type":"table","group":"g_findings","data":{"title":"Pricing oficial (Realtime API, mayo 2026)","columns":["Modelo","Precio","Uso"],"rows":[["gpt-realtime-translate","$0.034 / min audio","✅ El que usamos — speech-to-speech traducción"],["gpt-realtime-whisper","$0.017 / min audio","Streaming STT (no lo usamos)"],["gpt-realtime-2","$32/M in, $64/M out (tokens)","Voice agent conversacional (no lo usamos)"],["whisper-1 (legacy)","$0.006 / min","STT batch (no aplica)"]]}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"f3","type":"note","group":"g_findings","data":{"text":"<cite index=\"9-15,9-16,9-17\">gpt-realtime-translate is a live speech-to-speech translation model... It accepts spoken input, automatically detects the source language, and returns translated speech plus text transcripts. Developers only need to specify the target output language.</cite>\n\nFuente: developers.openai.com/cookbook/.../realtime_translation_guide"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"f4","type":"note","group":"g_findings","data":{"text":"📌 Detalle importante: <cite index=\"9-6\">If you want source-language transcripts alongside translated audio, configure input transcription with gpt-realtime-whisper.</cite>\n\nO sea: si ADEMÁS quieres el transcript del idioma origen (no solo el target), ahí sí se factura Whisper aparte. Hoy en el código solo consumimos `response.audio_transcript.*` (idioma destino) → **no incurrimos en costo de Whisper**."}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"f5","type":"note","group":"g_findings","data":{"text":"💡 Comparación contra DIY (STT+MT+TTS): <cite index=\"3-7,3-8,3-9\">The DIY alternative looks like: Deepgram or AssemblyAI STT in the source language, GPT-5.5 or Claude for translation, ElevenLabs Multilingual TTS for the output voice. That stack costs somewhere between $0.30 and $0.60 per minute on real workloads... Translate is roughly an order of magnitude cheaper for the live use case.</cite>","color":"#e8f7f0"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"g_costing","type":"group","data":{"label":"Modelo de costos correcto","icon":"fa-solid fa-calculator"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"c1","type":"note","group":"g_costing","data":{"text":"**Una sola variable** que medir: minutos de audio que cada listener mantiene abierta su sesión Realtime Translate.\n\nFórmula: `costo_meeting = Σ (minutos_sesion_listener) × $0.034`\n\nEjemplo: meeting de 30 min con 2 participantes = 2 × 30 × $0.034 = **$2.04**","color":"#f0f7ff"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"c2","type":"list","group":"g_costing","data":{"title":"Líneas que NO deberían estar en el doc de costos","items":[{"text":"❌ Whisper / STT por minuto (no se usa)"},{"text":"❌ TTS por carácter o por segundo (no se usa)"},{"text":"❌ Traducción MT (gpt-4o / gpt-5) por tokens (no se usa)"},{"text":"❌ Cualquier prorrateo STT+MT+TTS — eso era el modelo viejo"}]}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"c3","type":"list","group":"g_costing","data":{"title":"Líneas que SÍ aplican","items":[{"text":"✅ gpt-realtime-translate: $0.034 / min audio (una línea por listener-sesión)"},{"text":"➕ (opcional, si se activa) gpt-realtime-whisper: $0.017 / min para transcripción del idioma origen"},{"text":"➕ TURN/STUN bandwidth (infra propia, no OpenAI)"},{"text":"➕ Hosting Node/Express + MySQL (infra propia)"}]}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"g_action","type":"group","data":{"label":"Acciones recomendadas","icon":"fa-solid fa-arrow-right"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"a1","type":"task","group":"g_action","data":{"text":"Revisar el documento de costos: eliminar líneas de Whisper / TTS / MT separadas y dejar UNA sola línea de `gpt-realtime-translate @ $0.034/min`.","status":"todo"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"a2","type":"task","group":"g_action","data":{"text":"Confirmar en runtime que NO se está activando input transcription (gpt-realtime-whisper). Revisar el endpoint `POST /api/realtime/session` en el backend y verificar que el payload no incluya `input_audio_transcription`.","status":"todo"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"a3","type":"task","group":"g_action","data":{"text":"Decidir si las columnas legacy `stt_latency_ms`, `mt_latency_ms`, `tts_latency_ms` del schema se deprecan (DROP) o se reutilizan como `total_latency_ms` único. Hoy están vacías o mal interpretadas.","status":"todo"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"a4","type":"task","group":"g_action","data":{"text":"Instrumentar tracking de minutos consumidos por usuario/meeting para poder facturar y comparar contra el invoice real de OpenAI (que se ve en platform.openai.com → Usage).","status":"todo"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"g_sources","type":"group","data":{"label":"Fuentes","icon":"fa-solid fa-link"}}
{"cmd":"add","id":"src","type":"list","group":"g_sources","data":{"title":"Referencias","items":[{"text":"OpenAI – Realtime translation guide: developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/realtime-translation"},{"text":"OpenAI – Managing costs (Realtime): developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/realtime-costs"},{"text":"OpenAI – gpt-realtime-translate model page: developers.openai.com/api/docs/models/gpt-realtime-translate"},{"text":"OpenAI – Cookbook live translation: developers.openai.com/cookbook/examples/voice_solutions/realtime_translation_guide"},{"text":"OpenAI blog – Advancing voice intelligence (mayo 2026): openai.com/index/advancing-voice-intelligence-with-new-models-in-the-api/"},{"text":"TokenCost análisis pricing: tokencost.app/blog/openai-gpt-realtime-2-voice-pricing"}]}}
